channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Rethinking the positive role of cluster structure in complex networks for link prediction tasks
item.description: Specifically, we propose that it is easier to establish links between nodes with similar representation vectors and cluster tendencies in undirected graphs, while nodes in a directed graphs can more easily point to nodes similar to their representation vectors and have greater influence in their own cluster.

item.title: Materials Property Prediction with Uncertainty Quantification: A Benchmark Study
item.description: Uncertainty quantification (UQ) has increasing importance in building robust high-performance and generalizable materials property prediction models.

item.title: Rickrolling the Artist: Injecting Invisible Backdoors into Text-Guided Image Generation Models
item.description: We introduce backdoor attacks against text-guided generative models and demonstrate that their text encoders pose a major tampering risk.

item.title: Spatial-Temporal Convolutional Attention for Mapping Functional Brain Networks
item.description: To validate the performance of the proposed method, we evaluate the approach on HCP-rest dataset.

item.title: A Theoretical Study on Solving Continual Learning
item.description: Continual learning (CL) learns a sequence of tasks incrementally.

item.title: Dealing with Abbreviations in the Slovenian Biographical Lexicon
item.description: We also propose and present the results of a method for expanding the identified abbreviations in context.

item.title: Logits are predictive of network type
item.description: A classifier is then trained on the logit vectors of the trained set of this dataset to map the logit vector to the network index that has generated it.

item.title: PP-YOLOE-R: An Efficient Anchor-Free Rotated Object Detector
item.description: With multi-scale training and testing, PP-YOLOE-R-l and PP-YOLOE-R-x further improve the detection precision to 80. 02 and 80. 73 mAP.

item.title: Tensor Robust PCA with Nonconvex and Nonlocal Regularization
item.description: To this end, we integrate nonlocal self-similarity into N-TRPCA, and further develop a nonconvex and nonlocal TRPCA (NN-TRPCA) model.

item.title: The Path to Autonomous Learners
item.description: In this paper, we present a new theoretical approach for enabling domain knowledge acquisition by intelligent systems.

item.title: Evaluating and Improving Factuality in Multimodal Abstractive Summarization
item.description: Current metrics for evaluating factuality for abstractive document summarization have achieved high correlations with human judgment, but they do not account for the vision modality and thus are not adequate for vision-and-language summarization.

item.title: SSDA-YOLO: Semi-supervised Domain Adaptive YOLO for Cross-Domain Object Detection
item.description: Domain adaptive object detection (DAOD) aims to alleviate transfer performance degradation caused by the cross-domain discrepancy.

item.title: Benchmarking Quality-Diversity Algorithms on Neuroevolution for Reinforcement Learning
item.description: We present a Quality-Diversity benchmark suite for Deep Neuroevolution in Reinforcement Learning domains for robot control.

item.title: Real-Time Target Sound Extraction
item.description: We present the first neural network model to achieve real-time and streaming target sound extraction.

item.title: Soft Masking for Cost-Constrained Channel Pruning
item.description: Structured channel pruning has been shown to significantly accelerate inference time for convolution neural networks (CNNs) on modern hardware, with a relatively minor loss of network accuracy.

item.title: Data Models for Dataset Drift Controls in Machine Learning With Images
item.description: This can lead to speed up and stabilization of classifier training at a margin of up to 20% in validation accuracy.

item.title: Music Mixing Style Transfer: A Contrastive Learning Approach to Disentangle Audio Effects
item.description: We propose an end-to-end music mixing style transfer system that converts the mixing style of an input multitrack to that of a reference song.

item.title: SPEAKER VGG CCT: Cross-corpus Speech Emotion Recognition with Speaker Embedding and Vision Transformers
item.description: In this paper, we start from the general idea above and develop a new learning solution for SER, which is based on Compact Convolutional Transformers (CCTs) combined with a speaker embedding.

item.title: Rethinking the transfer learning for FCN based polyp segmentation in colonoscopy
item.description: Besides the complex nature of colonoscopy frames with intrinsic frame formation artefacts such as light reflections and the diversity of polyp types/shapes, the publicly available polyp segmentation training datasets are limited, small and imbalanced.

item.title: Data-free Defense of Black Box Models Against Adversarial Attacks
item.description: At test time, WNR combined with trained regenerator network is prepended to the black box network, resulting in a high boost in adversarial accuracy.

item.title: Convex Clustering through MM: An Efficient Algorithm to Perform Hierarchical Clustering
item.description: Convex clustering is a modern method with both hierarchical and $k$-means clustering characteristics.

item.title: Large Language Models Are Human-Level Prompt Engineers
item.description: By conditioning on natural language instructions, large language models (LLMs) have displayed impressive capabilities as general-purpose computers.

item.title: Translated Skip Connections -- Expanding the Receptive Fields of Fully Convolutional Neural Networks
item.description: The effective receptive field of a fully convolutional neural network is an important consideration when designing an architecture, as it defines the portion of the input visible to each convolutional kernel.

item.title: Single SMPC Invocation DPHelmet: Differentially Private Distributed Learning on a Large Scale
item.description: We show that locally training support vector machines (SVMs) and computing their averages leads to a learning technique that is scalable to a large number of users, satisfies differential privacy, and is applicable to non-trivial tasks, such as CIFAR-10.

item.title: Estimating the Carbon Footprint of BLOOM, a 176B Parameter Language Model
item.description: Progress in machine learning (ML) comes with a cost to the environment, given that training ML models requires significant computational resources, energy and materials.

item.title: Learning safety in model-based Reinforcement Learning using MPC and Gaussian Processes
item.description: In this work, we propose a method to encourage safety in a Model Predictive Control (MPC)-based Reinforcement Learning (RL) agent via Gaussian Process (GP) regression.

item.title: Computed tomography coronary angiogram images, annotations and associated data of normal and diseased arteries
item.description: Cases were classified as normal (zero calcium score with no signs of stenosis) or diseased (confirmed coronary artery disease).

item.title: Fast and robust Bayesian Inference using Gaussian Processes with GPry
item.description: GPry does not need any pre-training, special hardware such as GPUs, and is intended as a drop-in replacement for traditional Monte Carlo methods for Bayesian inference.

item.title: Efficient Spatially Sparse Inference for Conditional GANs and Diffusion Models
item.description: With 1. 2%-area edited regions, our method reduces the computation of DDIM by 7. 5$\times$ and GauGAN by 18$\times$ while preserving the visual fidelity.

item.title: INGREX: An Interactive Explanation Framework for Graph Neural Networks
item.description: Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) are widely used in many modern applications, necessitating explanations for their decisions.

item.title: Fair and Optimal Classification via Transports to Wasserstein-Barycenter
item.description: Our insight comes from the key observation that finding the optimal fair classifier is equivalent to solving a Wasserstein-barycenter problem under $\ell_1$-norm restricted to the vertices of the probability simplex.

item.title: Empirical Analysis of Model Selection for Heterogenous Causal Effect Estimation
item.description: Unlike model selection in machine learning, we cannot use the technique of cross-validation here as we do not observe the counterfactual potential outcome for any data point.

item.title: Fine-Tuning Language Models via Epistemic Neural Networks
item.description: These models learn a wide range of capabilities from training on large unsupervised text corpora.

item.title: Crosslingual Generalization through Multitask Finetuning
item.description: We find finetuning large multilingual language models on English tasks with English prompts allows for task generalization to non-English languages that appear only in the pretraining corpus.

item.title: FedTP: Federated Learning by Transformer Personalization
item.description: Instead of using a vanilla personalization mechanism that maintains personalized self-attention layers of each client locally, we develop a learn-to-personalize mechanism to further encourage the cooperation among clients and to increase the scablability and generalization of FedTP.

item.title: Log-density gradient covariance and automatic metric tensors for Riemann manifold Monte Carlo methods
item.description: When implemented in conjunction with a Riemann manifold variant of the recently proposed numerical generalized randomized Hamiltonian Monte Carlo processes, the proposed methodology is highly competitive, in particular for the more challenging target distributions associated with Bayesian hierarchical models.

item.title: Convolution channel separation and frequency sub-bands aggregation for music genre classification
item.description: In music, short-term features such as pitch and tempo constitute long-term semantic features such as melody and narrative.

item.title: Overcoming Barriers to Skill Injection in Language Modeling: Case Study in Arithmetic
item.description: Through their transfer learning abilities, highly-parameterized large pre-trained language models have dominated the NLP landscape for a multitude of downstream language tasks.

item.title: Robust Few-shot Learning Without Using any Adversarial Samples
item.description: These methods rely on the generation of adversarial samples in every episode of training, which further adds a computational burden.

item.title: Open-Vocabulary Argument Role Prediction for Event Extraction
item.description: Specifically, we formulate the role prediction problem as an in-filling task and construct prompts for a pre-trained language model to generate candidate roles.

item.title: MALUNet: A Multi-Attention and Light-weight UNet for Skin Lesion Segmentation
item.description: To address this challenge, we propose a light-weight model to achieve competitive performances for skin lesion segmentation at the lowest cost of parameters and computational complexity so far.

item.title: Continual Learning of Neural Machine Translation within Low Forgetting Risk Regions
item.description: Specifically, we propose two methods to search the low forgetting risk regions, which are based on the curvature of loss and the impacts of the parameters on the model output, respectively.

item.title: Exploring the State-of-the-Art Language Modeling Methods and Data Augmentation Techniques for Multilingual Clause-Level Morphology
item.description: While Transformer architectures with data augmentation and pipeline architectures achieved the best results for inflection and reinflection tasks, pipelines and prefix-tuning on mGPT received the highest results for the analysis task.

item.title: Galaxy Image Deconvolution for Weak Gravitational Lensing with Physics-informed Deep Learning
item.description: Removing optical and atmospheric blur from galaxy images significantly improves galaxy shape measurements for weak gravitational lensing and galaxy evolution studies.

item.title: Toward Unsupervised Outlier Model Selection
item.description: At its core, ELECT is based on meta-learning; transferring prior knowledge (e. g. model performance) on historical datasets that are similar to the new one to facilitate UOMS.

item.title: Embed and Emulate: Learning to estimate parameters of dynamical systems with uncertainty quantification
item.description: This paper explores learning emulators for parameter estimation with uncertainty estimation of high-dimensional dynamical systems.

item.title: Towards Discovering Neural Architectures from Scratch
item.description: The discovery of neural architectures from scratch is the long-standing goal of Neural Architecture Search (NAS).

item.title: A $k$-additive Choquet integral-based approach to approximate the SHAP values for local interpretability in machine learning
item.description: Besides accuracy, recent studies on machine learning models have been addressing the question on how the obtained results can be interpreted.

item.title: Verifying And Interpreting Neural Networks using Finite Automata
item.description: Verifying properties and interpreting the behaviour of deep neural networks (DNN) is an important task given their ubiquitous use in applications, including safety-critical ones, and their blackbox nature.

item.title: DPM-Solver++: Fast Solver for Guided Sampling of Diffusion Probabilistic Models
item.description: The commonly-used fast sampler for guided sampling is DDIM, a first-order diffusion ODE solver that generally needs 100 to 250 steps for high-quality samples.
